data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**Duplicate property names** across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get auto-uniquified column names (appended number). **Nested complex types** now include the full path (`Complex_NestedComplex_Property` instead of `NestedComplex_Property`).

Both generate renaming migrations. Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested: preserve the old shorter name
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, pb =>
    {
        pb.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City)
              .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City"); // was NestedComplex_Property, now would be Payment_BillingAddress_City
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging). Add it:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
}
```

Update all methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
